Added REST support to existing '
                               'modules
\n'
                               '
By default, the module will use REST if the '
                               'target system supports it, and the options are '
                               'supported.  Otherwise, it will switch back to '
                               'ZAPI.  This behavior can be controlled with '
                               'the use_rest option:\n'
                               '1. Always: to force REST.  The module fails '
                               'and reports an error if REST cannot be used.\n'
                               '1. Never: to force ZAPI.  This could be useful '
                               'if you find some incompatibility with REST, or '
                               'want to confirm the behavior is identical '
                               'between REST and ZAPI.\n'
                               '1. Auto: the default, as described above.
\n'
                               '
    \n'
                               '
  • na_ontap_ipspace
    • \n'

                               '-- Note: only enable and '

                               'REST

  • na_ontap_net_routes
    • \n'

  • na_ontap_qtree\n'
                               '-- Note: oplocks is not supported '

  • na_ontap_svm\n'

na_ontap_vserver_create
\n'
                              '
Create one or more Vservers.
\n'
                              '
Creates Vserver with specified protocol(s).  '
                              'Will join to Windows Domain provided AD '
                              'credintals are included.\n'
                              'Modifies default rule for NFS protocol to '
                              '0.0.0.0/0 ro to allow NFS connections
\n'
                              '
Requirements
\n'
                              '
Since this uses the NetApp ONTAP modules it '
                              'will require the python library netapp-lib as '
                              'well as the Ansible 2.8 release.
\n'
                              '
Role Variables
\n'
                              '
cluster: <short ONTAP name of '
                              'cluster>\n'
                              'netapp_hostname: <ONTAP mgmt ip or fqdn>\n'
                              'netapp_username: <ONTAP admin account>\n'
                              'netapp_password: <ONTAP admin account '
                              'password>\n'
                              '\n'
                              '#Based on if Variables != or == None determins '
                              'if a section runs.  Each variable will take one '
                              'or more dictonary entries.  Simply omit '
                              'sections\n'
                              "#that you don't want to run.  The following "
                              'would run all sections\n'
                              '\n'
                              'vservers: # Vservers to create\n'
                              '  - { name: nfs_vserver, aggr: aggr1, protocol: '
                              'nfs, aggr_list: "aggr1,aggr2" } # '
                              'aggr_list is optional.  If not specified all '
                              'aggregates will be added to the allowed list.\n'
                              '  - { name: cifs_vserver, aggr: aggr1, '
                              'protocol: cifs }\n'
                              '\n'
                              'vserver_dns: # DNS at the Vserver level.\n'
                              '  - { vserver: cifs_vserver, dns_domains: '
                              'lab.local, dns_nameservers: 172.32.0.40 }\n'
                              '\n'
                              'lifs: # interfaces for the Vservers being '
                              'created\n'
                              '  - { name: nfs_vserver_data_lif, vserver: '
                              'nfs_vserver, node: cluster-01, port: e0c, '
                              'protocol: nfs, address: 172.32.0.193, netmask: '
                              '255.255.255.0 }\n'
                              '  - { name: cifs_vserver_data_lif, vserver: '
                              'nfs_vserver, node: cluster-01, port: e0c, '
                              'protocol: nfs, address: 172.32.0.194, netmask: '
                              '255.255.255.0 }\n'
                              '\n'
                              'gateway: # To configure the default gateway for '
                              'the Vserver.\n'
                              '  - { vserver: nfs_vserver, destination: '
                              '0.0.0.0/0, gateway: 172.32.0.1 }\n'
                              '\n'
                              'cifs: # Vservers to join to an AD Domain\n'
                              '  - { vserver: cifs_vserver, cifs_server_name: '
                              'netapp1, domain: ansible.local, force: true }\n'
                              '\n'
                              'fcp: # sets FCP ports as Target\n'
                              '  - { adapter: 0e, node: cluster-01 }\n'
                              '
\n'
                              '\n'
                              '
Dependencies
\n'
                              '
The tasks in this role are dependent on '
                              'information from the na_ontap_gather_facts '
                              'module.\n'

na_ontap_snapmirror_create
\n'
                              '
Create or verify the following
\n'
                              '
Cluster peer\n'
                              'Vserver peer\n'
                              'Destination volume\n'
                              'Snapmirror relationship
\n'
                              '
Requirements
\n'
                              '
Since this uses the NetApp ONTAP modules it '
                              'will require the python library netapp-lib as '
                              'well as the Ansible 2.8 release.
\n'
                              '
Role Variables
\n'
                              '
src_ontap: # IP or FQDN of the '
                              'source ONTAP cluster\n'
                              'src_name: # Shortname of the source cluster \n'
                              'src_lif: # IP address of a source Intercluster '
                              'LIF\n'
                              'src_vserver: # Name of source Vserver\n'
                              'src_volume: # Name of source FlexVol\n'
                              'dst_ontap: # IP or FQDN of the destination '
                              'ONTAP cluster\n'
